node.text: Portobello Road Market is a must!

Virtual Tour: 8 Best Places To Shop In London. Swipe left to see!

Here’s a summary:
1. Bond Street: The best for high end shopping.
2. Oxford Street: The best for mid-market brands. 
3. Regent Street: The most beautiful shopping destination.
4. Bicester Village: The best for discount luxury goods.
5. Knightsbridge: The best for luxury department stores.
6. Covent Garden: The best for tourists.
7. Camden Market: The best for boho chic fashion.
8. Portobello Road Market: The best for antiques and collectibles.

Click on link in bio for more details.

Photo by Evan Tang on May 19, 2020. Image may contain: text that says '1. BOND STREET PRADA Bond Street is a famous shopping street lined with many many luxury boutiques. This is THE place for high end shopping. Famous brands: Burberry, Cartier, Chanel, Dior, Hermes, Jimmy Choo, Louis Vuitton, Prada Ralph Lauren, Tiffany & Co, etc.'

Photo by Evan Tang on May 19, 2020. Image may contain: text that says '2. OXFORD STREET This shopping street is home to hundreds of retail stores. It good place to shop for popular mid-market brands. Famous Brands & Stores: Selfridges, Primark, TK Maxx, Adidas, Gap, Bershka, Topshop, H&M, Uniqlo, Foot Locker, Zara, etc.'

Photo by Evan Tang on May 19, 2020. Image may contain: ‎one or more people and outdoor, ‎text that says '‎3. REGENT STREET ראT This This is the most beautiful shopping destination in London. It is home to many mid-market brands and luxury boutiques. Famous brands & stores: The Apple Store, H&M, Molton Brown, Ted Baker, Longchamp, Furla, Tory Burch, Desigual.‎'‎‎

Photo by Evan Tang on May 19, 2020. Image may contain: one or more people, text that says '4. BICESTER VILLAGE This famous outlet mall mall offers amazing discounts on luxury brands. It is less than an hour's train ride from London. Famous Brands: Coach, Jimmy Choo, Gucci, Burberry, Ferragamo, Michael Kors, Celine, and many more.'

Photo by Evan Tang on May 19, 2020. Image may contain: indoor, text that says '5. KNIGHTSBRIDE This district is home to luxury department stores and and high-end fashion boutiques. The famous Harrods store is located here! Famous brands & stores: Harrods, Harvey Nichols, Sloane Street, Topshop, Tommy Hilfiger Europe flagship store.'

Photo by Evan Tang on May 19, 2020. Image may contain: outdoor, text that says '6. COVENT GARDEN MIREN Covent Garden is the famous shopping and theatre district of London. This is a good place for tourists to shop and explore. Famous brands: Chanel, Burberry, Kate Spade, MAC, Michael Kors, Molton Brown, Mulberry, Zara.'

Photo by Evan Tang on May 19, 2020. Image may contain: one or more people and outdoor, text that says '7. CAMDEN MARKET CAMDIEN LOCK This huge market is a great place to shop for boho chic chic fashion items like vintage clothes and handcrafted jewellery. There are also also many independent independent stores selling books, music,furniture, and other eclectic items.'

Photo by Evan Tang on May 19, 2020. Image may contain: 1 person, text that says '8. PORTOBELLO MARKET ESTD 887 ALICE'S BEST- Located at Notting Hill, Portobello Road Market is sa a famous street market home to myriad of antiques and collectibles.
